verifyChainAndGetUserKey

  • verifyChainAndGetUserKey(certs: CertsChain, rootAddr: string, validAt: number, arrFactory?: nacl.arrays.Factory): object
    • Defined in lib-common/mid-sigs-NaCl-Ed.ts:275

    Parameters

      is a chain of certificate to be verified.

    • rootAddr: string

      is MailerId service's domain.

    • validAt: number

      is an epoch time moment (in second), at which user certificate must be valid. Provider certificate must be valid at creation of user's certificate. Root certificate must be valid at creation of provider's certificate.

    • Optional arrFactory: nacl.arrays.Factory

verifyKeyCert

  • verifyKeyCert(keyCert: SignedLoad, principalAddress: string, signingKey: Key, validAt: number, arrFactory?: nacl.arrays.Factory): JsonKey
    • Defined in lib-common/mid-sigs-NaCl-Ed.ts:344

    This function does verification of a single certificate with known signing key. If your task requires verification starting with principal's MailerId, use verifyPubKey function that also accepts and checks MailerId certificates chain.

    Parameters

    • keyCert: SignedLoad

      is a certificate that should be checked

    • principalAddress: string

      is an expected principal's address in a given certificate. Exception is thrown, if certificate does not match this expectation.

    • signingKey: Key

      is a public key, with which given certificate is validated cryptographically. Exception is thrown, if crypto-verification fails.

    • validAt: number

      is an epoch time moment (in second), for which verification should be done.

    • Optional arrFactory: nacl.arrays.Factory

      is an optional array factory.

    Returns JsonKey

    a key from a given certificate.

verifyPubKey

  • verifyPubKey(pubKeyCert: SignedLoad, principalAddress: string, certChain: CertsChain, rootAddr: string, validAt: number, arrFactory?: nacl.arrays.Factory): JsonKey
    • Defined in lib-common/mid-sigs-NaCl-Ed.ts:374

    Parameters

    • pubKeyCert: SignedLoad

      certificate with a public key, that needs to be verified.

    • principalAddress: string

      is an expected principal's address in both key certificate, and in MailerId certificate chain. Exception is thrown, if certificate does not match this expectation.

    • certChain: CertsChain

      is MailerId certificate chain for named principal.

    • rootAddr: string

      is MailerId root's domain.

    • validAt: number

      is an epoch time moment (in second), for which key certificate verification should be done.

    • Optional arrFactory: nacl.arrays.Factory

      is an optional array factory.

    Returns JsonKey

    a key from a given certificate.
